  -q, --quiet, --silent      Inhibit usual output
  -v, --verbose              Print more information
  -?, --help                 Give this help list
      --usage                Give a short usage message
  -V, --version              Print program version

Report bugs to <rtdmr6@@localhost.localdomain>.
@end example

@node Invoking smart_type, Problems, Sample, Top
@chapter Invoking @command{smart_type}
@cindex invoking
@cindex version
@cindex options
@cindex usage
@cindex help
@cindex getting help

The format for running the @command{smart_type} program is:

@example
smart_type @var{option} @dots{}
@end example

@code{smart_type} supports the following options:

@c Formatting copied from the Texinfo 4.0 manual.
@table @code
@item --output=@var{name}
@itemx -o @var{name}
Write output to @var{name} instead of standard output.

@item --quiet
@itemx --silent
@itemx -q
Inhibit usual output.

@item --verbose
@itemx -v
Print more information.

@item --directory=@var{directory}
Use the specified directory.

@item --help
@itemx -?
Print an informative help message describing the options and then exit
successfully.

@item --usage
Briefly list the options.

@item --version
@itemx -V
Print the version number of @command{smart_type} on the standard output
and then exit successfully.
@end table

